    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment is Accepted. The FEA framework demonstrates adequate predictive capability for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU. Eleven of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieved level 1 against a required level of 2; this shortfall is considered acceptable given the standardized and tightly controlled nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the strong output comparison results across three independent FEA codes. The Use error factor assessment was in progress and the factor evidence is incomplete, but the overall body of evidence is judged sufficient to support an Accepted decision for this Medium assurance level COU.",
